    "plan_content": "Here is the complete implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` with `parse` and `stringify`\n\n### What was found\n\nThe existing `src/ini.zig` **cannot be reused** — it requires a `bun.DotEnv.Loader` for `.npmrc` env-variable substitution, making it unsuitable as a public format parser. A fresh `src/interchange/ini.zig` is needed.\n\nAll four existing format namespaces (TOML, JSONC, JSON5, YAML) follow an identical pattern across **6 layers** of files. INI will slot in as the 5th format.\n\n---\n\n### Files to create (2)\n\n**`src/interchange/ini.zig`** — Self-contained line-by-line INI parser:\n- `pub fn parse(source, log, allocator) !Expr`\n- Handles: sections `[section]` and `[a.b]` (dot-separated → nested objects), `key = value`, comment lines starting with `;` or `#`, inline comments\n- Value coercion: `\"true\"`/`\"false\"` → `E.Boolean`, `\"null\"` → `E.Null`, numeric strings → `E.Number`, quoted strings → `E.String`, otherwise `E.String`\n- Returns an `Expr` (bun.ast) — same output type as all other interchange parsers\n\n**`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — JS namespace binding:\n- `create()` → object with `parse` + `stringify` properties\n- `parse` mirrors `JSONCObject.zig`: calls `INI.parse()`, converts via `Expr.toJS()`\n- `stringify` mirrors `YAMLObject.zig`: walks `JSValue`, emits top-level scalars as `key = value`, nested objects as `[section]` headers\n\n---\n\n### Files to modify (6)\n\n| File | What to add |\n|------|-------------|\n| `src/interchange.zig` | `pub const ini = @import(\"./interchange/ini.zig\");` |\n| `src/bun.js/api.zig` | `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");` |\n| `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | 4 locations: lazy prop decl, `@export`, getter fn, import alias |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | `macro(INI) \\` in `FOR_EACH_GETTER` (between `Glob` and `JSON5`) |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | `INI   BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI   DontDelete|PropertyCallback` in the table |\n| `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | `namespace INI { parse(input: string): object; stringify(input: object): string; }` after `namespace TOML` |\n\n---\n\n### Test file (1)\n\n`test/js/bun/ini/bun-ini-api.test.ts` — covers parse (sections, comments, type coercion, quoted strings), stringify (scalars, sections), and a round-trip `parse → stringify → parse` check.",
